[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering new features for Tapir Pekko**\n\nI'm thinking about adding new functionalities to the Tapir Pekko HTTP server. It currently handles various aspects like route paths, headers, errors, and more, but I wonder if it can support WebSockets. It seems like we might need public API dependencies, maybe even for file uploads and multipart data.\n\nI also find myself pondering a potential feature: converting multiple endpoints to a route without duplicating flows, possibly allowing for better error handling through the public API. This could simplify dynamic access a lot!\n\n**Evaluating testing needs**\n\nThe developer suggested adding tests to ensure that execution covers the uncovered dynamic-access call sites and dedicated class mapping. However, the user wants to modify an existing file instead. I need to consider whether we should follow the user's request and focus on just one file. It might also be useful to inspect the metadata dynamic report to guide any adjustments. Striking that balance seems crucial!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02340e59c3e2ebfa0169facfe93a3c81928360c10f40aef8b7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-s_wJsvhuaPuinfEDIgz_xuSDOXDfku379RCM8iFuwKM6WW4Fk6kPoRE02r2UQgET4RWXZoizqUUc8hRGC6dqm5P65DZPjEMj2SUlp3365RUwcR8Zj_cDQoqVWaOEs7MMu3HMRvg9nmNtEOzx-d75XDLJZK68HGC9feuhWrorQpIVRdI63Yq3hRMeqCQXYmGtmQAxhFKu5J0f2ZLD-rzbhJdCgayY6EpiGOJAB7WN6d7wN9PRPQKgiK4jOVMjSbIVQUoDKl7m2pU50GkIZG1xSJEOa1nA2GdFl4XpULnzKu9EyDZWpu_i2EkrESGIxYAEIslD_UJkBcDJHROthJifiopme_UEpfXQ51n0WBVKZD8wdtSCWsvURl4M4gYi43LaJIm2FcwJbPaGRqIIo4Ggen_y4NUtqiEnilaOIWidhEKLtnLaKNNipGtLz05qlo7cavo3luStIgV1V4fHm4Ugyqf34v8A5SsiXveOIdioJoipszbi0y33d7WOSGRoGO-57FFIXfdjBxye0lc-LNARL-qO5dS4T5zsGRCtF6yI5jfyFTKVnQN3pWwbP6KUaIMolQnLcDYDG2JoUxQKkfeSf1zLvfYoDgQYixXa6In3mGuOLVEiemhYrhXDdatW3SwrhiEH2_cdgMFQbAlf3nk2I7uwLQ3lIDbBNVX7Ad9FpEPmz0Ju9xYmGp3NjWiMJRW-GYsPsyT5lf